3  Example of Single Variable Prediction Using Logistic Regression

As talked about in previous chapters, we want to begin this study of fraud detection using as simple a model as possible, to get the idea across to the reader, then build from there.

To accomplish this we will be using packages from both R and Python to deal with modeling, analysis, validation and visualization.

Currently I am choosing not to hide code input so that this can be viewed inside the html doc, because I didn’t know how to share the work done otherwise, but this will change in later versions.
